reviews.text:
WHY DOSEN'T THE TICKET MACHINE TAKE CASH? TICKET OFFICED ONLY OPEN IN MORNING(but not on Sundays) BASICALLY MEANS WITHOUT A CARD YOU CANNOT BUY A TICKET FOR OVER HALF OF THE SERVICES FROM THIS STATION

staff when they are there are freindly and pleasent services rarelly cancelled

Poor station. No lifts for pram and disabled. Notorious delays and cancellations. Ticket machine broken very often. You might be charged and not receive your ticket as ticket office might be not opened or station staff not available. Toilet closed in the afternoon and permanently closed on weekends.

Small but well used station as direct links to Paddington.

Gets quite busy during work commuter times but handles ok.

Only one ticket machine though and that only accepts card. 
Ticket office open part time (mornings)

Good parking if needed.

Limited/no real facilities but does the job.
It's good not many delays but is a bit small could be bigger
